<P>
   NY-CREW-SEARCH (New York) _ News analysis: With speculation
already underway about potential successors to Schools Chancellor
Rudy Crew, members of the Board of Education and officials in Mayor
Giuliani's administration remain focused on the more immediate
question of who will actually carry out the search for a new
schools chief in an atmosphere that is expected to be even more
politically charged than usual. By David M. Herszenhorn.
</P>
<P>
   WHITE-CHRISTMAS (Darien, Conn.) _ The meteorologists may say
that there hasn't been any snow this winter in this quaint and
affluent town. But don't tell one resident's 11 grandchildren. Come
Christmas morning, they will discover a hill on their grandparents'
property blanketed with snow, giving them the perfect place to test
out their new sleds. But it's not Santa or even Mother Nature who
created their private winter wonderland. Instead, they can thank
the latest indulgence of the go-go '90s: a man-made, made-to-order
white Christmas. By David W. Chen.
</P>
