   &UR; CAMPAIGN _ (Moved in ``p'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MCCAIN-PRESS (Portsmouth, N.H.) _ Among political reporters, the
extraordinary access that John McCain provides has become the stuff
of instant legend. For hour after hour, he takes on all comers on
the bus his staff has christened Straight Talk Express. McCain will
spar and ruminate, banter and cajole, kick back and hold forth for
as long as anyone with a pad or a microphone cares. The result: an
unusually tension-free detente between the press and a candidate
from a wing of a party that often has viewed journalists as the
enemy. By Peter Marks. 2,000 words.
</P>
