   LASCHOOL-BOARD (Los Angeles) -- In the six months since a reform
slate took over the Los angeles Board of Education, the nation's
second-largest district has been partially disassembled and lays in
chaos. By Greg Gittrich (Will move on the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   TEACHER-GIFTS (Los Angeles) -- As her students squirmed through
the last few hours before winter break, teacher Gaby Calzadillas
examined her loot. Random tokens of her students' affection lay
heaped on her desk at Fenton Avenue Charter School. Body gel. A
wooden picture frame. A Pokemon card. One large bear. ``Oh, how
cute -- look, it's got `1999' on its paw!'' Calzadillas said. The
gifts may not always make sense, but the tradition of showering
presents upon teachers during the holiday season remains strong. By
David Baker (Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national
news wire.)
