<P>
   KWANZA-HOLIDAY (Los Angeles) -- Emphasizing family, community
and culture, the seven-day Kwanzaa celebration that begins today
leads African-Americans through a deeply reflective week where
family and philosophy overshadow presents. The few gifts that grace
the traditional Kwanzaa table in celebrants' homes are highly
symbolic: books and heritage symbols showing appreciation for
ancient African culture. Karenga founded the celebration in 1966 as
a black studies professor at California State University, Long
Beach. The festival has grown in popularity and is now celebrated
by more than 28 million people around the world. By Jesse Hiestand
(Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news wire.)
